WAYS YOU ARE SABOTAGING YOUR CAREER
.


What behavior do you consider to be inappropriate at work?

# Vocabulary
1. Sabotage (v) /ˈsæb.ə.tɑːʒ/: to ​damage or ​destroy ​equipment, ​weapons, or ​buildings in ​order to ​prevent the ​success of an ​enemy or ​competitor:
2. Procrastinate (v) /prəˈkræs.tɪ.neɪt/: to ​keep ​delaying something that must be done, often because it is ​unpleasant or ​boring:
3. Hesitate (v) /ˈhez.ɪ.teɪt/:  to ​pause before you do or say something, often because you are ​uncertain or ​nervous about it:
4. Inferior (adj) /ɪnˈfɪə.ri.ər/:  not good, or not as good as someone or something ​else:
5. Arrogant (adj) /ˈær.ə.ɡənt/:  ​proud in an ​unpleasant way and ​behaving as if you are ​better or more ​important than other ​people:
6. Impede (v) /ɪmˈpiːd/: to make it more ​difficult for something to ​happen or more ​difficult for someone to do something:
